article.headline: South Florida 93, Stetson 65
article.story: TAMPA, Fla. (AP) -- Terrence Leather and James Holmes combined for 45 points to lead South Florida past Stetson 93-65 Friday night. Leather scored 12 of his 21 points during a 23-2 run that gave South Florida (3-0) a 30-8 lead midway through the first half. He was perfect in eight shots from the floor, tying a school record. The Bulls collectively set a team mark by shooting 64.7 percent (33-for-51). They led 45-24 at the intermission. Their lead peaked at 32 late in the second half. Holmes made six of eight 3-point attempts and finished with 24 points Teammate Brian Swift added 15 and tied a career best with eight assists. Collin Dennis contributed 10 points, and junior college transfer Marius Prekevicius added eight assists for South Florida. Anthony Register led Stetson (1-1) with 20 points. Borislav Djordjic (16), Will Holloman (13) and E.J. Gordon (10) also scored in double figures for the Hatters. South Florida has opened with three victories for the fourth year in a row.
